issues located in 12A(3). }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 24.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 In relation to the \'91pure\'92 competition issues I have largely followed the version of the order suggested by the merging parties. These are located in section 1.1 of the order.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 25.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Paragraph 1.1.4 of the order relates to the efficiency issues, which the parties are alleging as part of their submissions. In argument counsel for the parties had no difficulty conceding this point, which was set out in the intervenor\'92s submission but not
 included in the parties draft. For this reason I need not justify its inclusion any further.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 26.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Paragraph 1.1.5 was included in the intervenor\'92 s notice, but not the parties. Since the efficiency considerations also involve in large part the better use of the Oryx railway line, which connects the iron ore mines to Saldanha Bay, it seems a logical cor
ollary to such an enquiry to hear if the arrangements lead to any adverse effects and hence the inclusion of 1.1.5. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 27.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Paragraph 1.1.6 serves to clarify issues of scope in the previous paragraphs and requires no further elaboration. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 28.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 In section 1.2, I set out the issues on which the intervenor may participate in relation to the public interest. Paragraph 1.2.1 again was common to both draft versions so I will not elaborate on it any further.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 29.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Paragraph 1.2.3 simply allows the intervenor to make any of its submissions, which it has made on the \'91pure competition\'92 grounds on public interest grounds as well. It would be artificial to classify them as purely one or the other as they could as easily 
be raised in terms of either sub-section. By way of example the Oryx railway line issues could also be relevant in terms of section 12A(3)(a). }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 30.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 However, if the length of submissions devoted to this issue in the heads of argument is anything to go by, then it is paragraph 1.2.2 that is the most contentious, and for this reason I have left it to last. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 31.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The intervenor, in its notice in which it indicated the issues on which it wished to participate, alleges that it has concerns about what it describes variously as Anglo\'92s \'91dominance\'92, \'91monopolization\'92 and further increase in the \'91concentration of ownershi
p and control\'92 in the mining industry. {\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s16{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 See paragraphs 6.1 and 7.1.}}}
{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 } It states that these are in conflict with national minerals policy and the Industrial Development Act, which is the statute establishing the intervenor. They then go on to raise these issues in much the same form in
 relation to the Competition Act, in paragraph 8, for which purpose they rely on extracts from the preamble and section 2 of the Act, which they argue locate these issues as being relevant to our merger consideration function.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s16{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs20\lang1033\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 The preamble of the Act contains references to past {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i \'93..excessive concentrations of ownership and control\'94 }and the need to {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i \'93regulate the transfer of ownership in keeping with the public interest\'94. }Section 2 inter-alia refers to the purpose of the Act being
 {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i \'93 to promote a greater spread of ownership, in particular to increase the ownership stakes of historically disadvantaged people.\'94}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs20\lang1033\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033 }}
{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 32.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The parties argue that our merger proceedings are not concerned with the objectives of either minerals legislation or the IDC\'92s statute, nor are the citations from the preamble and section 2 pertinent to our function in terms of section 12A. To see what we
 have to consider in terms of merger considerations we must confine ourselves to the language of section 12A and, looked at from that perspective these issues are not directly relevant and hence should not be part of the intervenor\'92s scope.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ul\ulc0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 33.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 I agree with the merging parties that we must consider the merger from the perspective of the Competition Act and not some other statute. {\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }}{{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The content of the IDC\'92s Act is relevant to the IDC\'92s interest, as I have recognized in my decision on its participation. To the extent that the IDC\'92s statutory objectives are co-extensive with those issues that we may consider under the Competition Act t
hey have an interest in raising those issues before us. (See paragraphs 36-40 of my decision dated 26 September 2002.) }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs20\lang1033\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033 }}
{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 34.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 I agree too, that we must confine our analysis to the framework of section 12A and that the preamble and the objectives cannot be used to found some other consideration not expressly or by implication located in that section.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 35.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Nevertheless section 12A is widely framed. The pure competition considerations although listed do not constitute a closed list, hence the use of the word {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i \'93..including.." }that precedes the introduction of the list in section 12A(2).}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 36.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls4\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The public interest considerations whilst drafted in terse language are broad in scope. For instance the phrase {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i \'93..effect on a particular industrial sector or region\'94 }opens up for consideration an enormous range of issues without doing any violence to the 
language. Given that 12A(2) contains a non-exhaustive list, and the wide ambit of 12A(3), it is a legitimate exercise in statutory interpretation to look at other parts of the statute, which set out its purpose and objectives, so as to create the lens thro
ugh which we should view the interpretation of section 12A. Indeed this is precisely the approach followed by Marais JA in his minority judgment in the {\ul\ulc0 Standard Bank} case, which involved the interpretation of a section relating to the application of the Co
mpetition Act.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s16{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch   }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0{\ul\ulc0 Standard Bank Investment Corporation Ltd v Competition Commission 2000 (2) SA 797 SCA}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 , page 816 - 817 }}}
{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af6\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af6\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 } }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 
